title.narrative: By the end of 2020 violence against children is reduced through integrated and coordinated prevention and protection mechanisms(Medical, psycho- social, and Legal).

description.narrative: UNICEF supported 164 child protection networks in 10 regions, an increase from 142 in 2019. 5,695 child victims of violence received psychosocial, medical and/or legal support services through these networks in target regions, surpassing the annual target of 5,000.; Support was continued for the functioning of the national toll-free child helpline, despite COVID-related constraints. Children’s clubs in 134 lower secondary schools in six regions were supported to undertake awareness raising activities on child protection. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:13/01/2021
